---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Methodology · State of AI Code Review"
  description="How the data was produced. Source, filters, privacy thresholds, reproducibility, and consent."
  runningHead="Methodology"
  page="Methodology"
>

  <section class="max-w-[1280px] mx-auto px-8 pt-16 md:pt-20 pb-12">
    <div class="grid grid-cols-12 gap-8 items-start">
      <div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-7">
        <div class="tracked text-ink-500 mb-4 reveal reveal-1">Apparatus</div>
        <h1 class="font-display leading-[0.98] tracking-tight text-ink-900 reveal reveal-2" style="font-size: clamp(3rem, 7vw, 6rem);">
          How the <span class="italic">data was produced.</span>
        </h1>
      </div>
      <aside class="col-span-12 md:col-span-5 md:pt-8 reveal reveal-3">
        <div class="border-l border-ink-900 pl-5">
          <p class="text-ink-700 leading-[1.6] text-[15px]">
            This section documents the dataset, filtering criteria, privacy thresholds, and citation format. All SQL queries are public on GitHub. External researchers can request a controlled extract under data use agreement at <a href="mailto:research@kodus.io" class="underline decoration-1 underline-offset-4 hover:text-oxblood-500">research@kodus.io</a>.
          </p>
        </div>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="max-w-[1280px] mx-auto px-8 pb-20">
    <div class="grid grid-cols-12 gap-10 border-t-2 border-ink-900 pt-16">

      <div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-3">
        <div class="tracked text-oxblood-500">§ i</div>
        <div class="tracked text-ink-500 mt-2">Source</div>
      </div>
      <div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-9">
        <p class="font-display italic text-ink-900 leading-[1.35]" style="font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 2.2vw, 2rem);">
          All data is sourced from the Kodus production code review pipeline.
        </p>
        <p class="text-ink-700 leading-[1.7] mt-5 max-w-prose">
          Kodus reviews pull requests across GitHub, GitLab, Bitbucket, and Azure DevOps. The full dataset lives in a BigQuery warehouse. Each chart in this report has a backing SQL query published in the <a href="https://github.com/kodustech/stateofcodereview.com" class="underline decoration-1 underline-offset-4 hover:text-oxblood-500">GitHub repository</a> under <code class="font-mono text-sm bg-paper-200 px-1.5 py-0.5">methodology/queries/</code>.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="col-span-12 border-t border-paper-300"></div>

      <div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-3">
        <div class="tracked text-oxblood-500">§ ii</div>
        <div class="tracked text-ink-500 mt-2">Engine cutoff</div>
      </div>
      <div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-9">
        <p class="font-display italic text-ink-900 leading-[1.35]" style="font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 2.2vw, 2rem);">
          Suggestions before 2025-09-01 are excluded.
        </p>
        <p class="text-ink-700 leading-[1.7] mt-5 max-w-prose">
          Kodus introduced a new label taxonomy in September 2025 with five canonical labels: bug, security, performance, cross-file, and kody rules. Suggestions generated before this cutoff used a different label set and a different LLM prompt. To keep findings interpretable as the current state of AI code review, all pre-cutoff suggestions are excluded.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="col-span-12 border-t border-paper-300"></div>

      <div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-3">
        <div class="tracked text-oxblood-500">§ iii</div>
        <div class="tracked text-ink-500 mt-2">Privacy thresholds</div>
      </div>
      <div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-9">
        <p class="font-display italic text-ink-900 leading-[1.35]" style="font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 2.2vw, 2rem);">
          Aggregation only. No identifiers.
        </p>
        <ul class="text-ink-700 leading-[1.75] mt-5 space-y-2 list-none max-w-prose">
          <li class="pl-7 relative"><span class="absolute left-0 top-0 font-mono text-oxblood-500">a.</span> No slice with fewer than 50 suggestions is published as a finding.</li>
          <li class="pl-7 relative"><span class="absolute left-0 top-0 font-mono text-oxblood-500">b.</span> Language slices with fewer than five distinct organizations are footnoted as low-confidence.</li>
          <li class="pl-7 relative"><span class="absolute left-0 top-0 font-mono text-oxblood-500">c.</span> Organization, repository, and pull-request identifiers are never exposed.</li>
          <li class="pl-7 relative"><span class="absolute left-0 top-0 font-mono text-oxblood-500">d.</span> Suggestion text shown in the report is reviewed for sensitive substrings (hostnames, customer identifiers, project names) before publication.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="col-span-12 border-t border-paper-300"></div>

      <div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-3">
        <div class="tracked text-oxblood-500">§ iv</div>
        <div class="tracked text-ink-500 mt-2">Sample sizes</div>
      </div>
      <div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-9">
        <p class="font-display italic text-ink-900 leading-[1.35]" style="font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 2.2vw, 2rem);">
          For the 2026-Q2 snapshot.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-6 border-t border-ink-900">
          {[
            ['Suggestions with feedback, post-filter', '17,773'],
            ['Distinct organizations', '200'],
            ['Distinct repositories', '639'],
            ['Programming languages', '103'],
            ['Bug findings', '14,560'],
            ['Security findings', '7,483'],
            ['Cross-file findings', '1,852'],
            ['Codified review rules', '7,276'],
            ['Organizations with codified rules', '610'],
          ].map(([k, v]) => (
            <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between border-b border-paper-300 py-2.5">
              <span class="text-ink-700">{k}</span>
              <span class="font-mono text-ink-900">{v}</span>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="col-span-12 border-t border-paper-300"></div>

      <div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-3">
        <div class="tracked text-oxblood-500">§ v</div>
        <div class="tracked text-ink-500 mt-2">Out of scope</div>
      </div>
      <div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-9">
        <p class="font-display italic text-ink-900 leading-[1.35]" style="font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 2.2vw, 2rem);">
          What is not included.
        </p>
        <ul class="text-ink-700 leading-[1.75] mt-5 space-y-2 list-none max-w-prose">
          <li class="pl-7 relative"><span class="absolute left-0 top-0 font-mono text-oxblood-500">a.</span> Suggestions from Kodus self-hosted deployments. The data warehouse covers Cloud only.</li>
          <li class="pl-7 relative"><span class="absolute left-0 top-0 font-mono text-oxblood-500">b.</span> Suggestions without explicit developer feedback. Unobserved suggestions are excluded because reception cannot be measured.</li>
          <li class="pl-7 relative"><span class="absolute left-0 top-0 font-mono text-oxblood-500">c.</span> Pull requests from organizations that opted out of research. Reserved as policy. None currently.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="col-span-12 border-t border-paper-300"></div>

      <div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-3">
        <div class="tracked text-oxblood-500">§ vi</div>
        <div class="tracked text-ink-500 mt-2">Citation</div>
      </div>
      <div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-9">
        <p class="font-display italic text-ink-900 leading-[1.35]" style="font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 2.2vw, 2rem);">
          How to cite.
        </p>
        <p class="font-mono text-sm bg-paper-200 border-l-2 border-oxblood-500 p-5 leading-relaxed mt-6 max-w-prose">
          State of AI Code Review (2026-Q2).<br />
          Research by Kodus.<br />
          https://stateofcodereview.com
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
